HEADWORD: Uncloud
<hw>Un*cloud"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>cloud</ets>.]</ety> <def>To free from clouds; to
unvail; to clear from obscurity, gloom, sorrow, or the like.</def>
<rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unclue</ent>⟦br⟧
